The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Hoshiarpur, March 3 (PTI): Jatinder Kumar, a Class XII student, disappeared on Wednesday from the Rajpur Bhaian Government Senior Secondary School where he was to sit for an examination. 

 The boy, when found in the evening, told police he was whisked away in a car while on his way to school. However, the boy later confessed that he had fallen in love with a schoolmate and feared that if he failed his parents might not send him to school again.

 Gandhinagar (PTI): MLA Kantilal Amrutiya, who is serving a life sentence for murder, is preparing for his 12th standard examination from a Gujarat prison. The MLA from Rajkot district was convicted by a lower court in 2004 for the murder of a BJP worker.

 Khammam (PTI): Nine persons, including three students, died on Thursday after consuming spurious toddy in Andhra Pradesh.Seven bodies were found near toddy trees in Kuppurai village while two youths died in hospital.

 Jammu (PTI): Army troops arrested a Hizb-ul Mujahideen sector commander in Doda district on Thursday. Liaquat Hussain Minta was arre-sted in Puneja village in Baderwah tehsil. Four others managed to escape. One hideout was busted in Kharsum and several weapons were seized, sources said.

 Guna (PTI): Two tribals were killed and 11 injured when lightning struck them at Hananpur village in Madhya Pradesh on Wednesday. Virendra Aadiwasi and Raina Bai were killed while the injured were rushed to hospital. A compensation of Rs 50,000 for the next of kin of the deceased was announced, police said.

 Sonepat (PTI): A woman was rushed to hospital after her seven-year-old son accidentally pulled the trigger of a licensed revolver on Thursday. She is said to be out of danger. Her husband had kept the revolver after cleaning it when her son found it and started playing with it. She was shot when she rushed to take the weapon from the child.

 Srinagar (PTI): A court has sentenced Mohammad Rafiq Najar to seven-years? rigorous imprisonment for kidnapping and raping a minor girl in June 2002.




